# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "As the door fell shut behind her, the desert faded and she was back home."
    new "As the door fell shut behind her, the desert faded and she was back home."

    old "She looked around at the familiar room and felt her heart surge."
    new "She looked around at the familiar room and felt her heart surge."

    old "She was glad to be home."
    new "She was glad to be home."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard the sound of laughter."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard the sound of laughter."

    old "Sarah was on edge."
    new "Sarah was on edge."

    old "There was nobody here, other than Samayra."
    new "There was nobody here, other than Samayra."

    old "Placing her feet down softly, so as to avoid any sound, she crept towards the sound."
    new "Placing her feet down softly, so as to avoid any sound, she crept towards the sound."

    old "Moving down the hallway, Sarah came upon a door that lead to one of the smaller libraries."
    new "Moving down the hallway, Sarah came upon a door that lead to one of the smaller libraries."

    old "More laughter."
    new "More laughter."

    old "Stepping into the library, Sarah felt the heat of the burning hearth, casting a warm glow across the room."
    new "Stepping into the library, Sarah felt the heat of the burning hearth, casting a warm glow across the room."

    old "Samayra was sitting in one of the chairs. They were so large, the small girl almost seemed to dissapear into them."
    new "Samayra was sitting in one of the chairs. They were so large, the small girl almost seemed to dissapear into them."

    old "She was laughing."
    new "She was laughing."

    old "And opposite her...a stranger."
    new "And opposite her...a stranger."

    old "Sarah rushed forward, blue flame pouring from her hand."
    new "Sarah rushed forward, blue flame pouring from her hand."

    old "Her voice boomed with impossible authority."
    new "Her voice boomed with impossible authority."

    old "The stranger, for his part, only turned his head and regarded her. Unimpressed."
    new "The stranger, for his part, only turned his head and regarded her. Unimpressed."

    old "Aah, Sarah Rose I suspect?"
    new "Aah, Sarah Rose I suspect?"

    old "He turned back to Samayra."
    new "He turned back to Samayra."

    old "You were right, she's quite something."
    new "You were right, she's quite something."

    old "Sarah looked confused from the man, to Samayra, back to the man."
    new "Sarah looked confused from the man, to Samayra, back to the man."

    old "You're in my house, so I suggest you answer my questions!"
    new "You're in my house, so I suggest you answer my questions!"

    old "Has Xan moved out?"
    new "Has Xan moved out?"

    old "Instantly, Sarah felt a nervousness grow inside of her."
    new "Instantly, Sarah felt a nervousness grow inside of her."

    old "What...no. Tell me, who you are instead of questioning me!"
    new "What...no. Tell me, who you are instead of questioning me!"

    old "The man stood up."
    new "The man stood up."

    old "In the light of the hearth, she saw him more clearly. Young, not much older than her in age, so she suspected."
    new "In the light of the hearth, she saw him more clearly. Young, not much older than her in age, so she suspected."

    old "He smiled. It was a genuine smile, the kind only few people had."
    new "He smiled. It was a genuine smile, the kind only few people had."

    old "My manners must have been lost to me on the road. My apologies. My name is Metis."
    new "My manners must have been lost to me on the road. My apologies. My name is Metis."

    old "I've had the pleasure of meeting your...companion."
    new "I've had the pleasure of meeting your...companion."

    old "He seemed amused at the word, referencing Samayra."
    new "He seemed amused at the word, referencing Samayra."

    old "She's been so kind as to receive me."
    new "She's been so kind as to receive me."

    old "Sarah turned to Samayra, who was smiling broadly."
    new "Sarah turned to Samayra, who was smiling broadly."

    old "Sarah yelled her name, scolding her."
    new "Sarah yelled her name, scolding her."

    old "You can't just let people into the house, it's dangerous!"
    new "You can't just let people into the house, it's dangerous!"

    old "She saw Samayra's smile fade, the girl turned her eyes to the floor."
    new "She saw Samayra's smile fade, the girl turned her eyes to the floor."

    old "I'm sorry, he just...he knocked on the door and it was raining outside...and I thought..."
    new "I'm sorry, he just...he knocked on the door and it was raining outside...and I thought..."

    old "It's okay...I'm not mad."
    new "It's okay...I'm not mad."

    old "This seemed to cheer Samayra up, if only a bit."
    new "This seemed to cheer Samayra up, if only a bit."

    old "Sarah turned back to the man who called himself Metis."
    new "Sarah turned back to the man who called himself Metis."

    old "Well...I don't know what business you have, but I suppose you can best be on your way."
    new "Well...I don't know what business you have, but I suppose you can best be on your way."

    old "Metis frowned."
    new "Metis frowned."

    old "Aah, that would be a tragedy. I was hoping to speak with Xan."
    new "Aah, that would be a tragedy. I was hoping to speak with Xan."

    old "He knew Xan by name. Knew the location of the house. His robes...odd. A mage, she suspected."
    new "He knew Xan by name. Knew the location of the house. His robes...odd. A mage, she suspected."

    old "Well, Xan is currently away."
    new "Well, Xan is currently away."

    old "Metis shrugged."
    new "Metis shrugged."

    old "I can wait a few more hours. Your friend is greatly entertaining. A princess of Bagrad! What a story."
    new "I can wait a few more hours. Your friend is greatly entertaining. A princess of Bagrad! What a story."

    old "He smiled at Samayra, who smiled back at being complimented."
    new "He smiled at Samayra, who smiled back at being complimented."

    old "Sarah looked at Samayra. The girl had an open heart and trusted easily. Sarah both liked and disliked those parts of her."
    new "Sarah looked at Samayra. The girl had an open heart and trusted easily. Sarah both liked and disliked those parts of her."

    old "I don't think it will be a matter of hours. More weeks or months."
    new "I don't think it will be a matter of hours. More weeks or months."

    old "Where did he go, exactly?"
    new "Where did he go, exactly?"

    old "He didn't tell me."
    new "He didn't tell me."

    old "You don't know where he went and yet you know it will be months?"
    new "You don't know where he went and yet you know it will be months?"

    old "Sarah frowned. She didn't like being interogated. Especially by a stranger."
    new "Sarah frowned. She didn't like being interogated. Especially by a stranger."

    old "Well, you seem to know Xan, don't you?"
    new "Well, you seem to know Xan, don't you?"

    old "A smile crept on his face."
    new "A smile crept on his face."

    old "Yes, my old mentor."
    new "Yes, my old mentor."

    old "Then you know how he can be. He's not exactly forthcoming with all his secrets."
    new "Then you know how he can be. He's not exactly forthcoming with all his secrets."

    old "For a moment, Metis paused."
    new "For a moment, Metis paused."

    old "Then he slowly nodded."
    new "Then he slowly nodded."

    old "Forgive me if I come across rude, I had simply hoped to discuss a matter with him, but he can be hard to find."
    new "Forgive me if I come across rude, I had simply hoped to discuss a matter with him, but he can be hard to find."

    old "If you have any message, I'll gladly pass it on to him."
    new "If you have any message, I'll gladly pass it on to him."

    old "Metis fell back into his chair, clearly having little intention of leaving."
    new "Metis fell back into his chair, clearly having little intention of leaving."

    old "Would that I could, but I fear the message is more private. Not that I don't trust you."
    new "Would that I could, but I fear the message is more private. Not that I don't trust you."

    old "He smiled as he spoke."
    new "He smiled as he spoke."

    old "There was something foxlike about his behavior."
    new "There was something foxlike about his behavior."

    old "But I had heard through the grapevine that he had taken a new apprentice. The stunning Sarah Rose."
    new "But I had heard through the grapevine that he had taken a new apprentice. The stunning Sarah Rose."

    old "Metis chuckled."
    new "Metis chuckled."

    old "He always had a thing for collecting royalty."
    new "He always had a thing for collecting royalty."

    old "Well, I hope I've impressed. If there is no more business then..."
    new "Well, I hope I've impressed. If there is no more business then..."

    old "Metis kicked off one of his boots."
    new "Metis kicked off one of his boots."

    old "Ooh please, surely you're not going to throw out a fellow member of the order? In weather like this?"
    new "Ooh please, surely you're not going to throw out a fellow member of the order? In weather like this?"

    old "Tell her, Samayra!"
    new "Tell her, Samayra!"

    old "Metis made an exaggerated sad face."
    new "Metis made an exaggerated sad face."

    old "Sarah saw Samayra look at her with pleading eyes."
    new "Sarah saw Samayra look at her with pleading eyes."

    old "Please, Sarah...he's our guest."
    new "Please, Sarah...he's our guest."

    old "You're right. I'm just tired from my trip."
    new "You're right. I'm just tired from my trip."

    old "A trip? Ooh, won't you pull up a chair and tell us?"
    new "A trip? Ooh, won't you pull up a chair and tell us?"

    old "I was in Nauyziri."
    new "I was in Nauyziri."

    old "Sarah spoke the name of the city as if that was enough to settle the matter."
    new "Sarah spoke the name of the city as if that was enough to settle the matter."

    old "Metis' face dropped."
    new "Metis' face dropped."

    old "Nauyziri? Ugh, what on earth would anyone want in that place?"
    new "Nauyziri? Ugh, what on earth would anyone want in that place?"

    old "Sarah left the question unanswered."
    new "Sarah left the question unanswered."

    old "Turned out to be nothing. As you said, the city was...unimpressive."
    new "Turned out to be nothing. As you said, the city was...unimpressive."

    old "Metis laughed."
    new "Metis laughed."

    old "You can say that again. It's a miracle there's anything left of that miserable ruin."
    new "You can say that again. It's a miracle there's anything left of that miserable ruin."

    old "Metis kicked off his other remaining boot."
    new "Metis kicked off his other remaining boot."

    old "He turned his feet towards the burning fire."
    new "He turned his feet towards the burning fire."

    old "Gods, that's good."
    new "Gods, that's good."

    old "I've been out on the road for too long. It's nice to be able to put my feet up for a change."
    new "I've been out on the road for too long. It's nice to be able to put my feet up for a change."

    old "I'm sure there's plenty of people out there that would put up a mage."
    new "I'm sure there's plenty of people out there that would put up a mage."

    old "The cities, sure. But the people in those small villages just think you're a freak."
    new "The cities, sure. But the people in those small villages just think you're a freak."

    old "I sleep fine in an open field, but after a while even my back starts to give out."
    new "I sleep fine in an open field, but after a while even my back starts to give out."

    old "He turned towards Samayra."
    new "He turned towards Samayra."

    old "You ever sleep out under the stars?"
    new "You ever sleep out under the stars?"

    old "You're missin out. You should ask your boss if she can take you out camping sometime."
    new "You're missin out. You should ask your boss if she can take you out camping sometime."

    old "Sarah sighed, she didn't much like his intrusion in her house."
    new "Sarah sighed, she didn't much like his intrusion in her house."

    old "But she also knew she couldn't just throw him out. Not only was it not proper, she also wasn't sure how strong he might be."
    new "But she also knew she couldn't just throw him out. Not only was it not proper, she also wasn't sure how strong he might be."

    old "A mage was always dangerous."
    new "A mage was always dangerous."

    old "Well, I'm certain there is a bedroom available for you somewhere in the house. You are more than welcome as our guest."
    new "Well, I'm certain there is a bedroom available for you somewhere in the house. You are more than welcome as our guest."

    old "She did her best to sound genuine."
    new "She did her best to sound genuine."

    old "Metis nodded."
    new "Metis nodded."

    old "A most kind offer, but I'll sleep here tonight if that is fine with you. The fire...it's awfully calming."
    new "A most kind offer, but I'll sleep here tonight if that is fine with you. The fire...it's awfully calming."

    old "Of course, make yourself at home."
    new "Of course, make yourself at home."

    old "Sarah looked sternly at Samayra."
    new "Sarah looked sternly at Samayra."

    old "Samayra, can I have a word."
    new "Samayra, can I have a word."

    old "Samayra looked like a child, caught by a strict parent."
    new "Samayra looked like a child, caught by a strict parent."

    old "Sarah and Samayra walked a small distance from Metis."
    new "Sarah and Samayra walked a small distance from Metis."

    old "When did he show up to the house?"
    new "When did he show up to the house?"

    old "Just...a few hours after you left."
    new "Just...a few hours after you left."

    old "Did he say anything more about himself? Did you tell him anything?"
    new "Did he say anything more about himself? Did you tell him anything?"

    old "No, we just talked. He was nice. He's actually very friendly if you get to know him."
    new "No, we just talked. He was nice. He's actually very friendly if you get to know him."

    old "Sarah looked at Metis, still sitting calmly by the fire. He seemed to have almost forgotten about them."
    new "Sarah looked at Metis, still sitting calmly by the fire. He seemed to have almost forgotten about them."

    old "Alright, well...I want you to be careful around him. We don't really know who he is."
    new "Alright, well...I want you to be careful around him. We don't really know who he is."

    old "Okay, I'll promise."
    new "Okay, I'll promise."

    old "Sarah turned around to leave."
    new "Sarah turned around to leave."

    old "Surprised, Sarah turned back to Samayra."
    new "Surprised, Sarah turned back to Samayra."

    old "You never told me what it was like...Nauyziri."
    new "You never told me what it was like...Nauyziri."

    old "Sarah suddenly felt a great deal of stress leaving her body."
    new "Sarah suddenly felt a great deal of stress leaving her body."

    old "Ever since she'd been there, she'd been on edge. Now back, she had still been on edge."
    new "Ever since she'd been there, she'd been on edge. Now back, she had still been on edge."

    old "Seeing Samayra genuinely ask about her was oddly comforting."
    new "Seeing Samayra genuinely ask about her was oddly comforting."

    old "I'll tell you in the morning, okay? I'm just...I'm so tired right now."
    new "I'll tell you in the morning, okay? I'm just...I'm so tired right now."

    old "The girl paused for a bit before speaking."
    new "The girl paused for a bit before speaking."

    old "Can I sleep in your bed tonight?"
    new "Can I sleep in your bed tonight?"

    old "Of course"
    new "Of course"

    old "Sarah extended her hand to Samayra and Samayra eagerly took it."
    new "Sarah extended her hand to Samayra and Samayra eagerly took it."

    old "Hand in hand, they walked back towards Sarah's room."
    new "Hand in hand, they walked back towards Sarah's room."

    old "It hadn't been the first time Samayra slept in her bed. Despite how big the house was, it just seemed to make sense."
    new "It hadn't been the first time Samayra slept in her bed. Despite how big the house was, it just seemed to make sense."

    old "In the twisting and shifting corridors, Sarah liked the idea that there was something...someone, that was constant."
    new "In the twisting and shifting corridors, Sarah liked the idea that there was something...someone, that was constant."

    old "Sarah began kicking off her clothes."
    new "Sarah began kicking off her clothes."

    old "She looked at Samayra who was undergoing her own bedtim ritual. Brushing her long black hair with a comb."
    new "She looked at Samayra who was undergoing her own bedtim ritual. Brushing her long black hair with a comb."

    old "The comb was in a Bagrad style. Sarah wasn't sure if the girl has managed to bring it with her in the end, or if it already belonged to the house."
    new "The comb was in a Bagrad style. Sarah wasn't sure if the girl has managed to bring it with her in the end, or if it already belonged to the house."

    old "Who knew, maybe it was here simply because Samayra wanted it to be. The house had a way of expecting desires before even the recipient knew."
    new "Who knew, maybe it was here simply because Samayra wanted it to be. The house had a way of expecting desires before even the recipient knew."

    old "I am very tired though."
    new "I am very tired though."

    old "I'm just saying..."
    new "I'm just saying..."

    old "Samayra looked at her, still brushing her hair."
    new "Samayra looked at her, still brushing her hair."

    old "Just saying you shouldn't be expecting anything tonight."
    new "Just saying you shouldn't be expecting anything tonight."

    old "She saw Samayra's face turn red."
    new "She saw Samayra's face turn red."

    old "I...I didn't...I would...never-"
    new "I...I didn't...I would...never-"

    old "Sarah laughed, interrupting Samayra's stuttering panic."
    new "Sarah laughed, interrupting Samayra's stuttering panic."

    old "You can be really mean, you know that?"
    new "You can be really mean, you know that?"

    old "Sarah crawled into the bed and pulled the covers back."
    new "Sarah crawled into the bed and pulled the covers back."

    old "Well, you wanna sleep in your own room then?"
    new "Well, you wanna sleep in your own room then?"

    old "Samayra quickly got up and crawled into bed with Sarah."
    new "Samayra quickly got up and crawled into bed with Sarah."

    old "Pfff, you're the one who shouldn't expect anything."
    new "Pfff, you're the one who shouldn't expect anything."

    old "Sarah laughed as she reached out with one arm, putting it under Samayra's head."
    new "Sarah laughed as she reached out with one arm, putting it under Samayra's head."

    old "Samayra eagerly made use of her arm pillow."
    new "Samayra eagerly made use of her arm pillow."

    old "Together they laid there for a while, exchanging small nothings."
    new "Together they laid there for a while, exchanging small nothings."

    old "To Sarah, it was exactly what she wanted."
    new "To Sarah, it was exactly what she wanted."

    old "Company, but not the kind that would try to wrench out her every inner thought."
    new "Company, but not the kind that would try to wrench out her every inner thought."

    old "Not long after, each of them genuinely exhausted, fell into a sleep. Their bodies still entwined."
    new "Not long after, each of them genuinely exhausted, fell into a sleep. Their bodies still entwined."

    old "Sorry, Samayra. I just...I really need to sleep and I sleep better alone."
    new "Sorry, Samayra. I just...I really need to sleep and I sleep better alone."

    old "She saw the dissapointment on her face."
    new "She saw the dissapointment on her face."

    old "Okay. I understand."
    new "Okay. I understand."

    old "Samayra turned and left."
    new "Samayra turned and left."

    old "Sarah sighed. Maybe she should have been nicer to the girl."
    new "Sarah sighed. Maybe she should have been nicer to the girl."

    old "She would sometimes forget that Samayra was likely dealing with her own trauma's too."
    new "She would sometimes forget that Samayra was likely dealing with her own trauma's too."

    old "She wandered back to her own room."
    new "She wandered back to her own room."

    old "When she got there, it felt empty. But peaceful."
    new "When she got there, it felt empty. But peaceful."

    old "Sarah fell down in the bed and pulled the covers close."
    new "Sarah fell down in the bed and pulled the covers close."

    old "She kicked off her clothes and casually strewed them across the floor."
    new "She kicked off her clothes and casually strewed them across the floor."

    old "She wanted her room to be a mess."
    new "She wanted her room to be a mess."

    old "Closing her eyes, sleep came swiftly for her."
    new "Closing her eyes, sleep came swiftly for her."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard the sound of crackling fire."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard the sound of crackling fire."

    old "There was nobody here, other than herself. Or at least, there shouldn't be anyone else."
    new "There was nobody here, other than herself. Or at least, there shouldn't be anyone else."

    old "More crackling fire."
    new "More crackling fire."

    old "Sitting in one of the chairs...a stranger."
    new "Sitting in one of the chairs...a stranger."

    old "He turned back to the fire."
    new "He turned back to the fire."

    old "Pleasure to meet you."
    new "Pleasure to meet you."

    old "Sarah looked confused at the man."
    new "Sarah looked confused at the man."

    old "I've taken advantage of your hospitality I'm afraid."
    new "I've taken advantage of your hospitality I'm afraid."

    old "He seemed amused at the word."
    new "He seemed amused at the word."

    old "How did you get in here?!"
    new "How did you get in here?!"

    old "With my key, of course."
    new "With my key, of course."

    old "Sarah watched as Metis pulled a key from his pocket and held it up. It seemed similar to her own."
    new "Sarah watched as Metis pulled a key from his pocket and held it up. It seemed similar to her own."

    old "She had never considered the basic fact that there might be other keys in the world."
    new "She had never considered the basic fact that there might be other keys in the world."

    old "I can wait a few more hours."
    new "I can wait a few more hours."

    old "Sarah shrugged, pretending to be casual."
    new "Sarah shrugged, pretending to be casual."

    old "Sarah sighed. The man wasn't leaving."
    new "Sarah sighed. The man wasn't leaving."

    old "A trip? Ooh, won't you pull up a chair and tell me?"
    new "A trip? Ooh, won't you pull up a chair and tell me?"

    old "Well, I'm certain there is a bedroom available for you somewhere in the house. You are more than welcome as my guest."
    new "Well, I'm certain there is a bedroom available for you somewhere in the house. You are more than welcome as my guest."

